title: Kimi (kimi-for-code) rejects assistant tool_call messages missing reasoning_content when thinking=enabled
---
## Summary

Observed in ~/.clawq/daemon.log multiple times today on postmortem agents
that use provider=kimi_coding model=kimi-for-code:

```
WARN Attempt 1/3 failed (Failure("LLM API error (HTTP 400):
     {\"error\":{\"message\":\"thinking is enabled but reasoning_content
     is missing in assistant tool call message at index 3\",
     \"type\":\"invalid_request_error\"}}"))
```

Each occurrence retries 3x, then bubbles as a postmortem agent error.

Kimi's thinking-enabled mode requires that every assistant message which
contains tool_calls ALSO carry a `reasoning_content` field. When the
history contains an assistant tool_call message that came from a model
that didn't emit reasoning (e.g. session resume from a different
provider, or the assistant didn't think this turn), Kimi rejects.

## Why this is becoming load-bearing right now

The briefing crons were just switched to kimi_coding:kimi-for-code via
a dedicated cron:briefing session_key (commit pending). If kimi runs
into this for a multi-turn briefing where a previous turn's tool_call
lacks reasoning_content, all briefings will start failing the same way
the postmortems did.

## Suggested fix

Either:

1. In the OpenAI-compat path in src/provider.ml — when target model is
   in a "kimi thinking" list, walk the history and for any assistant
   message with tool_calls that has no thinking field, inject a stub
   reasoning_content="" or strip the thinking-enabled body field for
   that request.

2. Or, simpler: detect the model name kimi-for-code (and kimi-for-coding)
   and disable thinking-mode signaling in the request body entirely.
   These models include reasoning in their normal output and don't
   need separate thinking-mode handling.

3. Or, if Kimi's API genuinely requires reasoning_content on every tool
   call: store and replay the thinking blob alongside tool_calls in
   memory.ml's persistence, then surface it in messages_to_json.

## Evidence

- ~/.clawq/daemon.log: search 'reasoning_content is missing' — 6+ hits
  starting around 01:00, all on __postmortem_teams sessions using
  kimi-for-code
- All occurrences fail at message index 3 — first multi-turn assistant
  in the postmortem history, which has tool_calls but no thinking
  (postmortem starts fresh)

## Risk if not fixed

Kimi-for-code becomes effectively unusable for any session that contains
prior tool_use turns from any other provider. Affects:
- Postmortem agent (current fallback after B635's temperature fix)
- Briefings (just migrated to kimi)
- Any user-initiated kimi session that touches tool_calls